---
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import '../../styles/main.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Graphic Content - Chapter 1 | Hacker1 v1.0</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Chapter 1: Sacred Geometry - Foundation principles of visual design and mathematical beauty." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}favicon.svg`} />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Century+Schoolbook&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="dark-mode graphic-background">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Home</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work`}>Finished Work</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/graphic`}>Graphic</a> → 
        Chapter 1
      </nav>
      
      <h1>Graphic Content - Chapter 1: Sacred Geometry</h1>
      
      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>The Mathematics of Creation</h2>
        <p>
          "He has made everything beautiful in its time." - Ecclesiastes 3:11
        </p>
        <p>
          Sacred geometry reveals the divine patterns underlying all creation. From the 
          golden ratio found in flower petals to the spiral of galaxies, mathematics 
          expresses the mind of God through visual beauty and structural harmony.
        </p>
        
        <blockquote class="highlight">
          "Great are the works of the Lord; they are pondered by all who delight in them." - Psalm 111:2
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section solution-background">
        <h2>SVG as Digital Scripture</h2>
        <p>
          Just as medieval illuminated manuscripts combined text and image to glorify God, 
          we use SVG graphics to create digital illuminations that reveal spiritual truths 
          through mathematical precision and artistic beauty.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Core Design Principles:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Golden ratio proportions reflecting divine harmony</li>
          <li>Fibonacci sequences echoing natural growth patterns</li>
          <li>Circular forms representing unity and eternity</li>
          <li>Spiral patterns showing spiritual progression</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Featured Geometric Forms:</h3>
        <div class="geometry-showcase">
          <div class="geometry-item">
            <div class="svg-demo">
              <svg width="200" height="200" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
                <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="80" fill="none" stroke="#D4AF37" stroke-width="3" opacity="0.8"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="60" fill="none" stroke="#8A5A5A" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.6"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="40" fill="none" stroke="#5A7A5A" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.6"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="20" fill="none" stroke="#7A5A7A" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.6"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4>Sacred Circles</h4>
            <p>Concentric circles representing the eternal nature of God and the expanding ripples of divine love.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="geometry-item">
            <div class="svg-demo">
              <svg width="200" height="200" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
                <path d="M 100 20 Q 150 50 180 100 Q 150 150 100 180 Q 50 150 20 100 Q 50 50 100 20" 
                      fill="none" stroke="#8A5A5A" stroke-width="3" opacity="0.8"/>
                <path d="M 100 40 Q 130 60 160 100 Q 130 140 100 160 Q 70 140 40 100 Q 70 60 100 40" 
                      fill="none" stroke="#D4AF37" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.6"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4>Fibonacci Spiral</h4>
            <p>The golden spiral found throughout creation, from nautilus shells to galaxy arms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section experimental-background">
        <h2>Color as Spiritual Language</h2>
        <p>
          Colors in sacred art carry deep meaning. Gold represents divine glory, blue 
          signifies heavenly wisdom, red embodies divine love, and green speaks of 
          life and growth. Our color palettes are chosen not just for aesthetics, 
          but for their spiritual significance.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Sacred Color Palette:</h3>
        <div class="color-showcase">
          <div class="color-item">
            <div class="color-swatch" style="background: #D4AF37;"></div>
            <span>Divine Gold - Glory and Majesty</span>
          </div>
          <div class="color-item">
            <div class="color-swatch" style="background: #4A6FA5;"></div>
            <span>Heavenly Blue - Wisdom and Truth</span>
          </div>
          <div class="color-item">
            <div class="color-swatch" style="background: #8B4A5A;"></div>
            <span>Sacred Red - Love and Sacrifice</span>
          </div>
          <div class="color-item">
            <div class="color-swatch" style="background: #5A7A5A;"></div>
            <span>Life Green - Growth and Renewal</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="navigation-section">
        <div class="nav-buttons">
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/written-ch1`} class="button is-light">← Previous: Written Chapter 1</a>
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/two-d-ch1`} class="button is-primary">Next: Two-D Chapter 1 →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Add the custom floating bottom navbar -->
    <Navbar />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: white;
  }

  h1 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #f0f0f0;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h3 {
    color: #d4af37;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section h4 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .highlight {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.1);
    border-left: 4px solid #d4af37;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .geometry-showcase {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .geometry-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .svg-demo {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .color-showcase {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .color-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .color-swatch {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  }

  .navigation-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .nav-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .button.is-light {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: #f0f0f0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-light:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-primary {
    background: #8b7355;
    color: white;
    border: 1px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .button.is-primary:hover {
    background: #a0845f;
  }

  /* Add padding to body to prevent navbar overlap */
  body {
    padding-bottom: 100px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .geometry-showcase {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    
    .color-showcase {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
